From: Steve <steventhanhtuan@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 19:39:30 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 12/17] task4: end-to-end acceptance tests for the publication
 gate

One synthetic two-agent run reproduces the report's evidence patterns
through the real manager pass: a verified pair grouped by tag overlap
(one representative, one see-also), an honest refuted note demoted, an
evidence-free synthesis served as unverified, a score-mismatch failure
ranked last; index tier order, stamps, settle-after-one-follow-up and
no tmp debris all asserted. Plus a mid-pass-edit lock-in test and a
strengthened manager-level flag-off control test.

Reviewed with mutation checks (tier swap, representative flip, dropped
clobber guard all caught). 73 gate tests, 702 full suite, ruff clean.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
